HEADWORD: Chin cough
<hw>Chin" cough"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[For <ets>chink cough</ets>;
cf. As. <ets>cincung</ets> long laughter, Scot. <ets>kink</ets> a
violent fit of coughing, akin to MHG. <ets>k⟦imac⟧chen</ets> to pant.
Cf. <er>Kinknaust</er>, <er>Cough</er>.]</ety> <def>Whooping
cough.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

